d892a361-0b11-433d-8b8f-5524afc536bd" inv:numbering="continue"><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_bc43dd64-ebdd-4d34-9533-9b52516ccabe" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Values</xref> listed are for the labelled, declared <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_01903228-f11f-4cf9-803d-baa7b9942f7e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Value</xref> of insulation.</li><li id="_84805a68-03a3-41b4-8218-f44a387c70e6">X = not permitted.</li><li id="_d2912dd2-f615-4b37-9083-c9f51dc1fa0e">This Table shows wall heights for single <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_5e26b102-19bc-463f-a7f9-e1a9f6f71f4d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref> dwellings. For two <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_9f6d0e46-833d-4bdf-af9f-ac47f08ffa76" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref> (or more) dwellings with a wall height up to 2.4 m, add R0.5 to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1420_0.4.0.xml#_e5acb40f-3d3d-4a3d-8987-f09f7eaadf77" id="_1e554c43-9520-454e-ae83-8fcd15feb6cb" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">R-Values</xref> given in this Table. For two storey (or more) dwellings with a wall height greater than 2.4 m, add R1.0. In both cases, the maximum insulation level must be not more than R2.7, or R3.1 if there is a reflective airspace.</li><li id="_0c66e837-ace9-4990-93df-5c6677cffbb8">Where an overhang of &gt; 600 mm is used, the values for &gt; 450 to ≤ 600 apply provided no more than 15% of the total opaque wall area of the dwelling (excluding windows/doors) is covered by overhangs &gt; 600 mm.</li></ol></desc-note></table-reference>